Instructions
- Use Next.js App Router dynamic route: `export async function GET(request: Request, { params }: { params: { id: string } })`.
- Call `getJob(params.id)`. If undefined, return 404.
- Return `NextResponse.json(job)` on success.
- This is the polling fallback used by `SseLogPanel` when `EventSource` fails.

Deliverable
- `app/api/jobs/[id]/route.ts` — GET handler for job state polling.

Implementation assumptions (explicit)
- This route file is in `app/api/jobs/[id]/route.ts` — a separate file from `app/api/jobs/[id]/stream/route.ts` which is in a subdirectory.
- Both route files share the same dynamic segment `[id]` but serve different endpoints.

Please produce production-ready TypeScript code consistent with the above.
